title nasim — SBX-01 ISOLATE Command

' Participants with box colors per C4 layer

note over participants
  Scope:          Sandboxed command execution
  Preconditions:  SandboxExecutor initialized, policy loaded
  Excludes:       Policy management (SBX-02), monitoring (SBX-03)
  Contexts:       Tool execution, shell command runs
  Rollback:       Kill sandbox process on timeout or violation
  Design:         Process isolation with namespace and cgroup
end note

== SBX-01 ISOLATE Command ==

AgentOrchestrator -> SandboxExecutor: execute(command, policy)
SandboxExecutor -> SandboxPolicy: apply_rules(policy)
SandboxPolicy --> SandboxExecutor: rules_applied
SandboxExecutor -> SandboxExecutor: create sandbox (namespace, cgroup)
SandboxExecutor -> SandboxExecutor: execute command in sandbox
SandboxExecutor --> AgentOrchestrator: execution_result(output, exit_code)

note over participants
  Flow:    Apply policy -> create sandbox -> execute -> return
  State:   preparing -> executing -> complete
  Failure: Policy violation -> kill sandbox, return violation error
  Success: Agent receives command output and exit code
end note

@enduml